data2017 = read.csv("../week-3/data/2017.csv")
highgdp<-c(data2017$Economy..GDP.per.Capita.>1)
hgdp<-data2017[highgdp,]
lowgdp<-c(data2017$Economy..GDP.per.Capita.<=1)
lgdp<-data2017[lowgdp,]
hgdp$GDP="hgdp"
lgdp$GDP="lgdp"
GDP=rbind(hgdp,lgdp)
ne<-c(1,2,3,4,5)
NE<-data2017[ne,]
asia<-c(33,79,55,51,26)
ASIA<-data2017[asia,]
nra<-c(7,14)
NRA<-data2017[nra,]
afr<-c(101,84,95,53,128)
AFR<-data2017[afr,]
#使用rbind將同樣欄位的表格接合
#創一個新欄位來分出兩個表格的不同
#這樣在group的時候才可以分別
ASIA$region = "ASIA"
NE$region = "NE"
NRA$region="NRA"
AFR$region="AFR"
CON = rbind(ASIA, NE,NRA,AFR)

以下用 t-test 檢驗不同gdp是否存在快樂指數差異

#此函數會預設進行 Welch校正，以處理兩樣本變異數不相同的問題
t.test(Happiness.Score ~ GDP,data= GDP)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  Happiness.Score by GDP
## t = 11.55, df = 151.15, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  1.276929 1.803962
## sample estimates:
## mean in group hgdp mean in group lgdp 
##           6.059643           4.519197
#可加上參數 var.equal=TRUE 來假設變異數同值(不做Welch校正)
t.test(Happiness.Score ~ GDP, data = GDP, var.equal = TRUE)
## 
##  Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  Happiness.Score by GDP
## t = 11.493, df = 153, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  1.275645 1.805247
## sample estimates:
## mean in group hgdp mean in group lgdp 
##           6.059643           4.519197
